</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #2c5b53;'>Economy &amp; Labor</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/covid-19-exposes-the-delicate-economic-balance-we-all-live-in-under-capitalism/">COVID-19 Exposes the Delicate Economic Balance We All Live in Under Capitalism</a>
</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #2c5b53;'>Economy &amp; Labor</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/ilhan-omar-bill-would-cancel-rent-and-mortgage-payments-for-duration-of-pandemic/">Ilhan Omar Bill Would Cancel Rent and Mortgage Payments for Duration of Pandemic</a>
</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #1958aa;'>Politics &amp; Elections</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/attorney-general-barr-refuses-to-release-9-11-documents-to-victims-families/">Attorney General Barr Refuses to Release 9/11 Documents to Victims&#8217; Families</a>
</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #2c5b53;'>Economy &amp; Labor</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/postal-workers-union-leader-warns-the-usps-could-be-dead-in-three-months/">Postal Workers Union Leader Warns the USPS Could Be Dead in Three Months</a>
</article>
</div>
</aside>
</div>
<div class="entry-content primary-content-column columns small-12 medium-8">
<p>Presidents always take credit for the positive things that happen on their watch, but Donald Trump has gone to a whole new level. He endlessly touted the &ldquo;best economy ever,&rdquo; even though, under his watch, we just saw the continuation of trends from the Barack Obama years.</p>
<p>There was a modest pickup in GDP growth, with the average for the first three years of the Trump administration being 2.5 percent, compared to an average of 2.3 percent in the last three years of the Obama administration. By contrast, the pace of job growth slowed, from 224,000 to 182,000 over the same period.</p>
<p>There was little change in most other macroeconomic variables between the two administrations, as we saw the gradual improvement in the labor market under the Obama years continue into the Trump years. That meant things were getting better on the whole. However, the hundreds of thousands of people who lost health insurance in the Trump years are likely to disagree with his boasts of the best economy ever, as are people facing crushing student loan debt.</p><div class="truth-post-content-high  inline-callout-container" id="truth-255792"><aside class=" callout inline-callout callout--subscribe callout--dark" id="truth-255396">
<h2>Don&rsquo;t miss a beat</h2>
<p>Get the latest news and thought-provoking analysis from <em>Truthout</em>.</p>
